Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.29,0:00:10.55,Default,,0,0,0,,This jam is really good.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.71,0:00:12.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.76,0:00:15.01,Default,,0,0,0,,It's homemade lingonberry jam.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.22,0:00:17.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Homemade...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.01,0:00:22.52,Default,,0,0,0,,I was told to show this to any guest who likes it.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.64,0:00:24.77,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the maker of the jam.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.31,0:00:26.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Who is he?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.69,0:00:29.02,Default,,0,0,0,,His name is Conrad.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.27,0:00:34.19,Default,,0,0,0,,There's an area just south of here where\Na lot of lingonberries grow.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.20,0:00:38.28,Default,,0,0,0,,At some point, that area became his.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.45,0:00:43.54,Default,,0,0,0,,He makes such a fantastic jam that I don't\Nsee how anyone could complain.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.75,0:00:49.38,Default,,0,0,0,,He really is a pleasant man and he's one of my few friends.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.17,0:00:53.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Showing people this picture was his idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.38,0:00:56.93,Default,,0,0,0,,He thinks that having people see\Nthe real jam maker, Conrad,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.93,0:00:58.89,Default,,0,0,0,,will make people want to buy his jam in the future.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.85,0:01:04.43,Default,,0,0,0,,So we'll have to come back here for some jam sometime.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.43,0:01:05.93,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.69,0:01:11.11,Default,,0,0,0,,He'll be thrilled to hear that.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.44,0:02:59.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Are they really going to invade this peaceful town?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.61,0:03:00.86,Monster-Title,,0,0,0,,{\fad(750,750)\pos(360,340)}The Peaceful House
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.77,0:03:03.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Invade? There are other means to their end.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.15,0:03:07.78,Default,,0,0,0,,There are cases where a single gun has destroyed towns.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.12,0:03:11.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Zweifelstadt in 1958.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.24,0:03:19.13,Default,,0,0,0,,They all thought that their neighbor was the killer.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.13,0:03:23.17,Default,,0,0,0,,The residents were all on edge just going through their normal daily activities.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.17,0:03:25.92,Default,,0,0,0,,They were all in a group hysteria.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.92,0:03:27.18,Default,,0,0,0,,One of them,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.18,0:03:30.47,Default,,0,0,0,,a man called Volg Rogner, shot his neighbor\Nwith a gun he bought for self-protection.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.10,0:03:33.85,Default,,0,0,0,,After that, no one could stop it.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.85,0:03:38.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Fire raged through the town, and everything\Nat hand was used as a weapon.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.52,0:03:43.78,Default,,0,0,0,,All the residents participated in the massacre.\NThere wasn't a single survivor.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.61,0:03:48.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that going to happen in this town?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.82,0:03:51.28,Default,,0,0,0,,We have to stop it,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.28,0:03:53.12,Default,,0,0,0,,before it starts.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.79,0:03:59.04,Default,,0,0,0,,It might have already started.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.63,0:04:09.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, pay up!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.09,0:04:11.89,Default,,0,0,0,,You have it! Now give it up!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.89,0:04:13.47,Default,,0,0,0,,No! That money's mine!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.47,0:04:15.97,Default,,0,0,0,,It's going to pay for your drunk dad's booze anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.89,0:04:19.69,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not good for your health to drink so much.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.69,0:04:21.60,Default,,0,0,0,,This is an intervention.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.19,0:04:25.32,Default,,0,0,0,,You want to go get some grub.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.48,0:04:25.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.41,0:04:34.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Boy.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.54,0:04:37.75,Default,,0,0,0,,You hate them, don't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.08,0:04:43.38,Default,,0,0,0,,You hate them enough to kill them, don't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.76,0:04:50.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Where are you going?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.97,0:04:53.14,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm going to go talk to Conrad.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.60,0:04:55.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Talk about what?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.64,0:05:01.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Didn't you notice Ralph and the customers\Ngrinning at us at his cafe?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.77,0:05:05.90,Default,,0,0,0,,That's because it's rare to see us together as a couple.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.19,0:05:13.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Who knows what they'll do if they find out\Nwe won 20 million marks in the lotto.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.28,0:05:14.87,Default,,0,0,0,,D-Don't...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.87,0:05:20.62,Default,,0,0,0,,I have to talk to him rather than continue living in paranoia.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.91,0:05:25.88,Default,,0,0,0,,We don't even know if he knows that I won.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.88,0:05:27.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Then what are you going to do?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.17,0:05:31.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll pay him off.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.72,0:05:33.89,Default,,0,0,0,,That way he'll keep his mouth shut.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.22,0:05:38.85,Default,,0,0,0,,What if Conrad gets greedy and keeps\Nasking us for more money?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.18,0:05:41.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Th-Then I'll...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.02,0:05:42.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Then you will what?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.64,0:05:46.02,Default,,0,0,0,,I-I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.74,0:05:52.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn't it around here?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.65,0:05:55.49,Default,,0,0,0,,The place where he picks lingonberries.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.03,0:05:57.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Honey.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.16,0:05:58.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.29,0:06:02.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Conrad's a pretty good person.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.17,0:06:09.21,Default,,0,0,0,,He's not the kind who'd try to cash in on our good fortune.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.34,0:06:11.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn't that right, honey?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.85,0:06:22.23,Default,,0,0,0,,What's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.82,0:06:30.23,Default,,0,0,0,,You didn't!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.23,0:06:31.44,Default,,0,0,0,,It wasn't me!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.44,0:06:33.95,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't believe you've done something\Nyou can never take back!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.53,0:06:36.11,Default,,0,0,0,,I told you it wasn't me!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.12,0:06:37.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Then who did it?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.95,0:06:41.29,Default,,0,0,0,,How should I know? I haven't even\Nshot my gun since I bought it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.04,0:06:48.58,Default,,0,0,0,,What an annoying dog.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.59,0:06:50.84,Default,,0,0,0,,It's pissing me off.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.84,0:06:52.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm so irritated.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.22,0:07:00.81,Default,,0,0,0,,You seem to be in good spirits today.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.77,0:07:04.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Did anything good happen?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.23,0:07:07.02,Default,,0,0,0,,He finally appeared.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.02,0:07:08.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Who appeared?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.98,0:07:14.28,Default,,0,0,0,,A wonderful man who will take me away from here.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.08,0:07:22.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Alcohol. Alcohol.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.54,0:07:24.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Dammit.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.21,0:07:31.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm the laughing stock of this whole town.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.75,0:07:34.38,Default,,0,0,0,,This isn't cool at all...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.10,0:07:45.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Alcohol.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.43,0:07:47.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn't this...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.24,0:07:58.15,Default,,0,0,0,,what you really want?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.58,0:08:07.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Your son already took one.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.55,0:08:15.46,Default,,0,0,0,,A gunshot.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.51,0:08:21.51,Default,,0,0,0,,The dog isn't barking anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.28,0:08:36.61,Default,,0,0,0,,That was great.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.70,0:08:39.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Lipsky.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.16,0:08:45.16,Default,,0,0,0,,You're Franz Bonaparta's son, aren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.29,0:08:48.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Tell me where to find your father.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.79,0:08:50.21,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a race against time.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.67,0:08:53.13,Default,,0,0,0,,If I don't hurry, something horrible is going to happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.46,0:08:57.71,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, don't you Mr. Lipsky,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.71,0:08:59.42,Default,,0,0,0,,where you father is.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.05,0:09:05.51,Default,,0,0,0,,That doll is based on Nina, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.89,0:09:10.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Nina told me you were here.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.19,0:09:12.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Nina...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.78,0:09:17.69,Default,,0,0,0,,The curtain...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.28,0:09:19.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Could you open it for me?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.99,0:09:20.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.28,0:09:24.62,Default,,0,0,0,,How long have I been like this?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.08,0:09:26.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't worry about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.95,0:09:30.12,Default,,0,0,0,,You need to rest.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.87,0:09:32.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.71,0:09:37.04,Default,,0,0,0,,I know that you've been watching out for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.42,0:09:40.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't worry about me.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.38,0:09:42.09,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.18,0:09:45.01,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not trying to kill myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.60,0:09:49.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Dr. Reichwine and Dieter will be here soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.31,0:09:51.14,Default,,0,0,0,,What about you?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.06,0:09:53.10,Default,,0,0,0,,I have to go.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.60,0:09:54.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Where?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.65,0:09:56.90,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.32,0:10:01.36,Default,,0,0,0,,You were looking at a lot of materials\Nover there, weren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.53,0:10:03.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you figure anything out?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.74,0:10:07.99,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm okay, so talk to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.04,0:10:16.83,Default,,0,0,0,,I got some information from people affiliated with\Nthe former Czechoslovakian secret police in Prague
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.84,0:10:19.84,Default,,0,0,0,,and from a subordinate of General Wolf.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.67,0:10:22.76,Default,,0,0,0,,About Franz Bonaparta?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.01,0:10:28.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. He's a very mysterious man, but I think\NI was able to put together a profile on him.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.68,0:10:34.89,Default,,0,0,0,,He's a German-Czechoslovakian.  It seems that Franz Bonaparta is an alias as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.90,0:10:42.45,Default,,0,0,0,,After WWII, many German-Czeckoslovakians were chased out of their Bohemian homeland,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.45,0:10:45.20,Default,,0,0,0,,but his family remained.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.57,0:10:52.08,Default,,0,0,0,,It's unclear what role he played in the communist Czechoslovakian government.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.21,0:10:59.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I know that he married a Czech woman and had a child.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.75,0:11:09.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I know the child is one of the students who participated\Nin his first reading seminars in the '60s.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.52,0:11:15.64,Default,,0,0,0,,"Bonaparta has a son in Prague."
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.64,0:11:21.57,Default,,0,0,0,,I think that Peter Capek's last words were about that son.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.57,0:11:25.90,Default,,0,0,0,,This is a copy of an old photo, but I have a photograph of the boys
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.90,0:11:29.37,Default,,0,0,0,,who participated in the reading seminars in the '60s.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.28,0:11:33.95,Default,,0,0,0,,The kid on the left is...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.95,0:11:35.83,Default,,0,0,0,,"The unexceptional child."
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.96,0:11:41.79,Default,,0,0,0,,He was an unexceptional child, so he couldn't\Nparticipate in the reading seminars anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.80,0:11:42.71,Default,,0,0,0,,You know him?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.67,0:11:47.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Bonaparta had no use for him.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.34,0:11:50.47,Default,,0,0,0,,It's probably a man I know in Prague.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.68,0:11:56.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Does he know where his father... where Bonaparta is?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.48,0:11:57.94,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.94,0:12:01.40,Default,,0,0,0,,But he is your best lead.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.40,0:12:04.28,Default,,0,0,0,,If you don't hurry, something horrible is going to happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.78,0:12:05.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Something horrible?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.11,0:12:08.49,Default,,0,0,0,,I know...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.49,0:12:10.74,Default,,0,0,0,,what Johan is trying to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.16,0:12:11.99,Default,,0,0,0,,What is that?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.12,0:12:14.49,Default,,0,0,0,,The perfect suicide.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.54,0:12:17.62,Default,,0,0,0,,True solitude.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.62,0:12:19.29,Default,,0,0,0,,A true expression of love.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.29,0:12:24.96,Default,,0,0,0,,If you don't hurry, many innocent people will die.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.43,0:12:30.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Your bookshelf.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.01,0:12:35.01,Default,,0,0,0,,You have a lot of books written by Bonaparta\Nunder his many pen names.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.47,0:12:37.81,Default,,0,0,0,,I've read many of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.56,0:12:41.73,Default,,0,0,0,,The more I read, the more I notice something.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.77,0:12:45.82,Default,,0,0,0,,I wondered why they all have German names.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.40,0:12:50.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Klaus Poppe's "The God of Peace."\NIt's that way in this book, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.28,0:12:54.49,Default,,0,0,0,,The problem is with this pen name, Klaus Poppe.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.58,0:13:00.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Franz Bonaparta and all the other pen names are all Czech.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.75,0:13:03.25,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the only pen name that's German.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.96,0:13:12.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Could it be that Klaus Poppe is your\NGerman-Czechoslovakian father's real name?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.31,0:13:21.35,Default,,0,0,0,,There was a detective who figured out my father's\Nreal name using the same line of reasoning.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.81,0:13:22.52,Default,,0,0,0,,A detective?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.94,0:13:25.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Inspector Lunge from the BKA.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.52,0:13:26.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Lunge!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.73,0:13:27.65,Default,,0,0,0,,He was here?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.07,0:13:30.69,Default,,0,0,0,,He left weeks ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.70,0:13:31.74,Default,,0,0,0,,He left?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.03,0:13:34.28,Default,,0,0,0,,He also figured it out.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.28,0:13:39.37,Default,,0,0,0,,No, it's more like he became the person,\Nrather than figured it out.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.58,0:13:44.62,Default,,0,0,0,,"I am Klaus Poppe. I have no place to go home to."
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.63,0:13:49.46,Default,,0,0,0,,"In order to take back the tranquility in my heart,\NI have to return to my heart's homeland."
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.80,0:13:55.43,Default,,0,0,0,,German-Czechoslovakians lost their homeland\Nafter Germany lost the war.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.30,0:13:58.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Where in Germany are his ancestors from?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.22,0:14:01.10,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know that many details.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.10,0:14:04.69,Default,,0,0,0,,When I was little, my father said this:
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.65,0:14:09.73,Default,,0,0,0,,"Our home is a town surrounded by\Nmountains in South Germany."
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.49,0:14:15.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I had no use for it, so I gave it to Inspector Lunge.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.45,0:14:18.74,Default,,0,0,0,,A postcard I received about 3 or 4 years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.79,0:14:21.58,Default,,0,0,0,,It had no return address.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.58,0:14:25.83,Default,,0,0,0,,There was a hand-drawn sketch of\Na town from a mountain-top view.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.83,0:14:27.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Signed KP.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.54,0:14:29.50,Default,,0,0,0,,KP.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.46,0:14:32.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Klaus Poppe.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.51,0:14:35.72,Default,,0,0,0,,That's all I know.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.93,0:14:37.64,Default,,0,0,0,,South Germany.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.64,0:14:39.30,Default,,0,0,0,,A city surrounded by mountains.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.31,0:14:43.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Is my... Is my father going to be killed?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.02,0:14:44.89,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.85,0:14:47.65,Default,,0,0,0,,But it won't end there.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.65,0:14:51.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Nina... Is she safe?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.19,0:14:54.74,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to give this doll's drama a happy ending.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.99,0:14:57.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Please protect her.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.03,0:14:58.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.37,0:15:02.08,Default,,0,0,0,,What's going to happen?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.91,0:15:08.33,Default,,0,0,0,,He is... Johan's trying to recreate it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.33,0:15:11.09,Default,,0,0,0,,The tragedy at the Red Rose Mansion.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.09,0:15:13.67,Default,,0,0,0,,The massacre at 511 Kinderheim.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.01,0:15:15.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Please...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.01,0:15:20.51,Default,,0,0,0,,no matter what happens, please come back alive, Tenma.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.43,0:15:25.48,Default,,0,0,0,,You saved me, so you, too, should...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.07,0:15:33.73,Default,,0,0,0,,It's starting...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.15,0:15:36.70,Default,,0,0,0,,to rain.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.75,0:15:53.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Alcohol! Get me alcohol!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.30,0:15:55.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Dammit.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.97,0:16:01.85,Default,,0,0,0,,What happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.85,0:16:04.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Have the police found Conrad's body?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.81,0:16:08.85,Default,,0,0,0,,No, they still consider him missing\Nand they're looking for him.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.85,0:16:12.15,Default,,0,0,0,,I knew we shouldn't have hidden the body in the woods.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.15,0:16:14.23,Default,,0,0,0,,We should have gone straight to\Nthe police when we found him.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.23,0:16:16.07,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you saying?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.07,0:16:18.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Even you thought I shot him!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.11,0:16:22.16,Default,,0,0,0,,We're in this situation because you had to play the lotto!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.16,0:16:25.49,Default,,0,0,0,,You're the one who bought the guns!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.09,0:16:35.13,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not going to come, no matter how long you wait.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.17,0:16:39.13,Default,,0,0,0,,The bridge has been flooded because of this heavy rain.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.13,0:16:41.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Even traffic has been stopped by the flood.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.26,0:16:47.85,Default,,0,0,0,,So this is a solitary island.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.98,0:16:50.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Klaus Poppe?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.02,0:16:52.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you know of him?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.23,0:16:54.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Jakub Farobek...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.07,0:16:55.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Emil Scherbe...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.15,0:17:04.17,Default,,0,0,0,,I think they are all the same person.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.35,0:17:07.37,Default,,0,0,0,,The drawing and literary styles are different, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.91,0:17:11.12,Default,,0,0,0,,But you notice these things when\Nyou've seen as many as I have.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.12,0:17:14.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I have no idea why he uses so many pen names though.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.09,0:17:19.80,Default,,0,0,0,,The pictures are nice, but I don't like his books very much.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.30,0:17:23.72,Default,,0,0,0,,There are many picture books with dark topics.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.72,0:17:27.76,Default,,0,0,0,,But, this man's books are different.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.97,0:17:29.31,Default,,0,0,0,,How are they different?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.73,0:17:34.15,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a lot of malice.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.36,0:17:38.53,Default,,0,0,0,,One more thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.95,0:17:46.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Helmuth Voss's picture book.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.41,0:17:48.49,Default,,0,0,0,,It was released in '89.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.95,0:17:52.96,Default,,0,0,0,,There weren't many printed, so it\Nwas very hard for me to obtain.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.96,0:17:56.00,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the same person as Klaus Poppe.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.17,0:17:59.00,Default,,0,0,0,,How do you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.55,0:18:03.63,Default,,0,0,0,,You just notice these things.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.63,0:18:07.22,Default,,0,0,0,,People's style shows up no matter how hard\Nthey try to make the art look different.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.14,0:18:10.85,Default,,0,0,0,,The content is completely different from\Nthe other books he has written.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.85,0:18:14.27,Default,,0,0,0,,A thief sneaks into a mountain town.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.27,0:18:17.94,Default,,0,0,0,,He plans to steal the money from the people there,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.94,0:18:21.90,Default,,0,0,0,,but as he lives with the people there, he forgets how to steal.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.90,0:18:27.16,Default,,0,0,0,,He then lives a quiet life working\Nfor the people of the town.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.53,0:18:30.49,Default,,0,0,0,,The title is "A Restful Home."
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.62,0:18:34.00,Default,,0,0,0,,The disturbing feeling you get after reading\Nhis books is completely gone.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.00,0:18:37.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Too bad his art isn't very good.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.50,0:18:39.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn't it strange?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.46,0:18:42.63,Default,,0,0,0,,When his stories get good, his art gets bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.05,0:18:47.47,Default,,0,0,0,,It seems like he lost sight of his goal.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.35,0:18:50.26,Default,,0,0,0,,"A Restful Home."
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.26,0:18:51.68,Default,,0,0,0,,A town in the mountains.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.64,0:18:57.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Our home is a town surrounded by\Nmountains in South Germany.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.98,0:19:01.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Get me a map.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.11,0:19:01.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.99,0:19:05.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you have a map of South Germany?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.66,0:19:09.24,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you looking for?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.78,0:19:12.20,Default,,0,0,0,,A town in the mountains of South Germany.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.45,0:19:14.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Here it is!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.46,0:19:18.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Ruhenheim.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.84,0:19:23.22,Monster-Title,,0,0,0,,{\fad(375,0)\an8}Ruhenheim\N(A restful home)
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.84,0:19:28.18,Default,,0,0,0,,It sure is pouring out!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.18,0:19:33.18,Default,,0,0,0,,How is it? Have you found Conrad yet?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.31,0:19:35.14,Default,,0,0,0,,I have no idea where he is.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.56,0:19:38.23,Default,,0,0,0,,My partners are still looking for him...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.23,0:19:40.69,Default,,0,0,0,,but not in this rain.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.02,0:19:44.78,Default,,0,0,0,,The rails and the roads are all flooded by the river.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.28,0:19:47.20,Default,,0,0,0,,You must be worried about your friend.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.11,0:19:50.03,Default,,0,0,0,,What's going on here?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.03,0:19:51.95,Default,,0,0,0,,This town is normally so peaceful.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.45,0:19:56.79,Default,,0,0,0,,First, Conrad goes missing.\NThen Mrs. Hillman's dog is shot.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.67,0:20:01.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Mrs. Hillman is so upset that she can't even get out of bed.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.21,0:20:06.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Last night, Mr. Kemner was attacked after he left the pub.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.80,0:20:08.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I heard he was in critical condition.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.80,0:20:12.35,Default,,0,0,0,,We don't know who did it.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.35,0:20:17.64,Default,,0,0,0,,If Mr. Kemner dies, it will be the first murder in this town.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.27,0:20:21.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Because of this rain, we can't get any help.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.19,0:20:23.52,Default,,0,0,0,,What am I supposed to do when I don't have enough men?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.36,0:20:26.69,Default,,0,0,0,,It has to be outsiders.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.69,0:20:29.49,Default,,0,0,0,,There's never even been a crime in this town before.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.49,0:20:31.24,Default,,0,0,0,,It has to be the work of outsiders.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.24,0:20:33.62,Default,,0,0,0,,We're outsiders.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.04,0:20:38.83,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't mean you.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.83,0:20:40.33,Default,,0,0,0,,It sure is pouring out.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.92,0:20:44.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't go outside at all in my wheel chair.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.76,0:20:52.68,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll go find my partners and make another round.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.05,0:20:54.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Be careful!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.86,0:21:04.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Your husband's shoes...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.86,0:21:07.19,Default,,0,0,0,,are pretty dirty.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.44,0:21:10.61,Default,,0,0,0,,It's as if he was walking in the rain.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.74,0:21:14.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm going to borrow the phone.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.97,0:21:32.26,Default,,0,0,0,,That alcoholic.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.26,0:21:35.18,Default,,0,0,0,,He's not the kind who'd try anything funny.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.78,0:21:48.90,Default,,0,0,0,,What's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.90,0:21:50.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you out of gas?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.70,0:21:52.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Or are you out of oil?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.03,0:21:55.74,Default,,0,0,0,,I could call a repairman...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.42,0:22:05.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Another gunshot...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.59,0:22:13.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I couldn't get through.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.01,0:22:20.27,Default,,0,0,0,,We cant stop it...
